"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-2024-0812-1464523-olympics-closing-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Movie star Tom Cruise rappelled from the roof of France's national stadium and received the Olympic flag, bringing a heavy dose of Hollywood to the closing ceremony of the Paris Games as the French capital handed over to the next host Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13, \"end\": 23, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}, {\"begin\": 51, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9975616355105398, \"rank\": 0.0013370085925669848, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1634323532553972e-15, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 193, \"end\": 199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.914120504125938, \"rank\": 0.058612684580352827, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 237, \"end\": 248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2609268278387169e-19, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise made his leap, drawing gasps from spectators as he dropped 50 metres to the floor of the Stade de France, in the finale to a ceremony that blended the traditional, the obscure and the razzle dazzle of Tinseltown.\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Paris used iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower and the Palace of Versailles to win the hearts of Olympians and spectators alike, LA was swift to turn to its star draw: A-list celebrities.\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.525232767803636e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris was bringing down the curtain on an Olympic Games that brought scintillating sport to the heart of the capital, breathing new life into an Olympic brand hurt by the difficulties of Rio de Janeiro's 2016 Games and the soulless spirit of Tokyo's Covid-hit event.\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.525232767803636e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1710806898852432e-22, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999880873943008, \"rank\": 1.1912741972579589e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Culture of peace'  The two weeks of sporting drama saw China and the United States duke it out for top spot in the medal table right down to the last event.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999394279412822, \"rank\": 5.0625363654247114e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9991662822782703, \"rank\": 0.0008290289083518749, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the world emerged from the Covid pandemic in 2022, Paris had promised an Olympic \\\"light at the end of the tunnel\\\" and to provide the stage for a carefree Games.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999999999481588, \"rank\": 5.173948653126139e-11, \"text\": \"Covid pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}, {\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.525232767803636e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Russia's war in Ukraine on Europe's eastern flank, conflict in the Middle East, and France's heightened state of security alert loomed large as the Games got under way.\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9991874567014329, \"rank\": 0.0008116871162084584, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1285, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999637042894883, \"rank\": 3.609450045662744e-05, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 1353, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9975616355105398, \"rank\": 0.0013370085925669848, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International Committee President Thomas Bach saluted the athletes as he declared the Games closed.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1484, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"During all this time, you lived peacefully together under one roof in the Olympic Village.\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1615, \"end\": 1630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.802859294120011e-19, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You embraced each other,\\\" Mr Bach said.\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1661, \"end\": 1665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.7876114143428852e-12, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You respected each other, even if your countries are divided by war and conflict.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You created a culture of peace.\\\"\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"High bar for Los Angeles  \\\"Your mission, should you choose to accept it, is to bring the Olympic flag to Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1907, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1803, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2609268278387169e-19, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 1895, \"end\": 1906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2609268278387169e-19, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tom Cruise:#Paris2024#LA28#ClosingCeremonypic.twitter.com/bLsZJTc0xy  Cruise's exit on a motorbike saw the closing ceremony transition to a prerecorded video of the 62-year-old skydiving down to the Hollywood sign, where a wide shot showed the Olympic rings incorporated into the LA landmark.\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 2200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2107, \"end\": 2121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flag was then passed from US Olympians past and present as it traversed the city before reaching a beach party, where the LA music icons the Red Hot Chili Peppers, Billie Eilish, and Snoop Dogg and Dr Dre performed.\", \"from\": 2202, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2232, \"end\": 2234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9914587533571435, \"rank\": 0.005250423215285598, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}, {\"begin\": 2370, \"end\": 2383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}, {\"begin\": 2389, \"end\": 2399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dr Dre\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dr._Dre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles Mayor Karen Bass has acknowledged Paris has set a high standard, but the City of Angels has billed itself as a beacon of diversity and will have Hollywood to fall back on.\", \"from\": 2423, \"to\": 2606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2423, \"end\": 2434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2609268278387169e-19, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}, {\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.525232767803636e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1634323532553972e-15, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sporting memories  The Games were Team Ireland's most successful ever, with the country capturing seven medals overall.\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ireland competed in more sports than ever; and won more medals than ever before too, finishing the games a remarkable 19th on the overall medals table.\", \"from\": 2729, \"to\": 2880, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2729, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999992210394645, \"rank\": 7.78955271194827e-07, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosts France will take away fond sporting memories themselves.\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2888, \"end\": 2894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9975616355105398, \"rank\": 0.0013370085925669848, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French had a new golden boy to celebrate with swimmer L\\u00e9on Marchand emerging as the king of the pool, before French judoka Teddy Riner reigned supreme as he claimed his fifth Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 3144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2950, \"end\": 2956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.914120504125938, \"rank\": 0.058612684580352827, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3004, \"end\": 3017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999997803538704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L\\u00e9on Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9on_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 3059, \"end\": 3065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.914120504125938, \"rank\": 0.058612684580352827, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3073, \"end\": 3084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles put her twisties misery of Tokyo behind her, making a long-awaited Olympic return in front of a star-studded crowd.\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3186, \"end\": 3191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999880873943008, \"rank\": 1.1912741972579589e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She arrived the world's most decorated gymnast and left with a further three gold medals for her trophy cabinet.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking made its Olympic debut - to some derision on social media - whilst 3x3 basketball, sports climbing, skateboarding and surfing made their second appearances.\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Taoiseach to greet Irish Olympians at homecoming event at GPOLatest Olympics stories  The IOC will be relieved that no major scandals erupted, although it did have to grapple with some controversies.\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3586, \"end\": 3591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999843829105732, \"rank\": 1.1715704645088327e-05, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 3657, \"end\": 3660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0667885471958557e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A simmering doping row involving Chinese athletes hung over the Olympic swimming meet where the United States faced the biggest challenge to their reign in decades.\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3801, \"end\": 3808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9363423132038716, \"rank\": 0.06788243911409027, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3864, \"end\": 3877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9991662822782703, \"rank\": 0.0008290289083518749, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A storm around gender eligibility hit the women's boxing competition, revealing the toxic relations between the IOC and a widely discredited International Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4046, \"end\": 4049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0667885471958557e-38, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4075, \"end\": 4107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8657798262428207e-17, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, a clean-up of the Seine rewarded Paris with the optics of triathlon and marathon swimmers competing in the river through central Paris, without a wave of illness ensuing.\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4139, \"end\": 4144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5068837578139363e-14, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 4154, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.525232767803636e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4250, \"end\": 4255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.525232767803636e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:Reuters    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 4323, \"to\": 4413, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4348, \"end\": 4371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"